article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 90, Jacksonville St. 67
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Terry Evans scored a career-high 16 points and Josh Lawrence added 15 to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay to a 90-67 victory over Jacksonville State Wednesday night at the Oneida Casino Holiday Classic. Ryan Evanochko scored 15 points and Mike Schachtner added in 13 for Green Bay (6-6). The Phoenix hit 9 of its first 10 shots in jumping out to a 23-7 lead, and the only miss in that stretch resulted in an Evans tip dunk. The Gamecocks (3-8) never were closer than 12 points the rest of the game. Tracy Thomas led Jacksonville State with 11 points, and DeAndre Bray added 10 points, nine assists and seven rebounds. Erwin Staten and Jeremy Harris also had 10 points apiece. Green Bay has won four of its last five games and five straight home contests. The Phoenix is averaging 85.4 points per game in its home win streak.
